The paper discusses the use of parallel algorithms for solving optimization problems in various fields, including finance, logistics, production, and design. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of (meta)heuristic methods, which are commonly used in the field of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the need for unifying frameworks for parallel optimization across methodologies, application fields, and problems, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the paper suggests research directions for parallel optimization, which is related to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
